# Project Structure and Working Agreements

- Primary service is [boss_service.py](mdc:boss_service.py) exposing FastAPI app `app` and encapsulating Playwright lifecycle.
- Client CLI and SDK is [boss_client.py](mdc:boss_client.py).
- Service launcher is [start_service.py](mdc:start_service.py) (launches external Chrome with CDP and uvicorn --reload).
- Key docs to read/maintain each session:
  - Architecture: [docs/architecture.mermaid](mdc:docs/architecture.mermaid)
  - Technical specs: [docs/technical.md](mdc:docs/technical.md)
  - Tasks: [tasks/tasks.md](mdc:tasks/tasks.md)
  - Status: [docs/status.md](mdc:docs/status.md)
  - Changelog: [changelog.md](mdc:changelog.md)
- Configuration lives in [src/config.py](mdc:src/config.py) and support modules under [src/](mdc:src/).
- Tests live under [test/](mdc:test/).
- Demo and ops notebook is [command.ipynb](mdc:command.ipynb).

Conventions:
- Edit existing files unless a new module is clearly justified.
- Use absolute paths when referencing files in tools where possible.
- After implementing features, update status and add tests.
